Function Reference/sanitize key « WordPress Codex
-----------

Sanitize a string key. Keys are used as internal identifiers.

Lowercase alphanumeric characters, dashes and underscores are allowed.
Uppercase characters will be converted to lowercase. After
`sanitize_key()` has done its work, it passes the sanitized key through
the
[sanitize\_key](/index.php?title=Plugin_API/Filter_Reference/sanitize_key&action=edit&redlink=1 "Plugin API/Filter Reference/sanitize key (page does not exist)")
filter.

Usage
-----

` <?php sanitize_key( $key ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$key` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) String key
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 (string) 
:   Sanitized key

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

### Filters

-   **`'sanitize_key'`**:\
    `apply_filters( 'sanitize_key', $key, $raw_key )`

Change Log
----------

Since: 3.0.0

Source File
-----------

`sanitize_key()` is located in `/wp-includes/formatting.php`.

